	Viralheat is a venture-backed social media analytics and intelligence firm based in San Mateo, California. Viralheat is a powerful, simple, yet affordable way for brands, agencies, marketers and content producers to measure, analyze and engage the social web. Viralheat&#39;s intelligence platform is connecting businesses, large and small, to the social web and changing the way business is done.</p>
<p>
	We are looking for a Senior Software Engineer with a desire to build robust, scalable, and exciting social media intelligence platform. Thousands of small and medium businesses depends on Viralheat to draw actionable insights an understand how to engage with social media. Viralheat is aggregating data from the largest social media sites in the world, we aggregate and process over 200 million mentions a week today and it&#39;s growing at a mind boggling rate. We not only aggregate the data, we store, search, process and analyze the data in real-time. We push the edge of high scale cloud computing and deliver unparalleled data crunching power to our customers at a very low cost. You will be working on all aspects of our back-end technology stack including, aggregating new data sources, doing real-time search and computing analytics in real-time.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<p>
	&bull; Develop the next generation social media intelligence platform.<br />
	&bull; Drive and participate in requirements, architecture, and design specification reviews.<br />
	&bull; Analyze and improve efficiency, scalability, and stability of real-time data collection, storage, and retrieval processes.<br />
	&bull; Contribute to building an enterprise-class data storage, analysis and processing for Viralheat&rsquo;s cloud computing infrastructure.<br />
	&bull; Collaborate with the engineering team to design and implement product features in a fast-paced environment following agile development methodology.<br />
	&bull; Stay ahead of scalability and performance issues.<br />
	&bull; Use noSQL and other cutting edge technologies for solving scalability challenges with massive data sets<br />
